component changes stellar ages and SFRs by up to a factor of 10, and
dust attenuations by up to a factor of 2.5. Finally, we show that the
strength of our model AGN component correlates with independent AGN
indicators, suggesting that these galaxies truly host AGN. Notably, only
46\% of the SED-detected AGN would be detected with a simple MIR color
selection. Based on these results, we conclude that SED models which fit
MIR data without AGN components are vulnerable to substantial bias in
their derived parameters.},
