  abstract = {In this paper, we test the age matching hypothesis that the star 
formation rate (SFR) of a galaxy of fixed stellar mass is determined by
its dark matter halo formation history, e.g. more quiescent galaxies
reside in older haloes. We present new Sloan Digital Sky Survey
measurements of the galaxy two-point correlation function and
